<SLUG> BC-FBC-USC-NOTES-LADN </SLUG>
 
McCUTCHEON FACES ANOTHER CHALLENGE 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ There may be the impression he was burned by
Florida State's Peter Warrick, but USC cornerback Daylon McCutcheon
said he still feels like he's having an excellent season.
</P>
<P>
   McCutcheon will receive another stiff test Saturday when he
faces California's Dameane Douglas, the third-leading wide receiver
in the Pacific-10 Conference.
</P>
<P>
   McCutcheon's not feeling any pressure, however, even if the
public perception had Warrick getting the best of the Trojans' top
defensive back two weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't even think about it. I played a good game against
Florida State,'' McCutcheon said. ``He caught three passes (on me)
and they threw at me seven times.''
</P>
<P>
   Last week, McCutcheon graded out at a score of 82 against
Arizona State. He gave up a deep ball, but also broke up a
fourth-and-goal pass attempt.
</P>
<P>
   ``They threw at me eight times and had three completions. And I
had three deflections,'' McCutcheon said. ``I don't want to give up
any catches, but I think I played a good game.''
</P>
<P>
   McCutcheon's role may be expanding in the near future.
</P>
<P>
   If tailback Chad Morton doesn't improve soon, USC coach Paul
Hackett said he might have to ponder some other options _ including
McCutcheon on offense.
</P>
<P>
   ``Daylon is one (possibility),'' Hackett said. ``(Freshman
tailback) Sultan McCullough is another. If Chad's no better, we'll
have to be concerned about that.''
</P>
<P>
   Morton update: Morton showed improvement Thursday after
receiving treatment on his back. He will run today and Hackett said
he will make a game-time decision on whether Morton will play
against California.
</P>
<P>
   USC clarified Morton's injury Thursday, terming it a ``lumbar
contusion.'' The injury occurred when Morton was hit in the back
while scoring a touchdown against Florida State.
</P>
<P>
   It is not related to the back strain he suffered last month
while doing leg squats, although it was originally said to be a
re-aggravation.
</P>
<P>
   If Morton does not play, and his condition does not improve next
week, USC will consider an MRI test on his back. He has already
undergone X-rays.
</P>
<P>
   Hackett said he had not decided if Petros Papadakis or Frank
Strong would start.
</P>
<P>
   Bowen to start: With right tackle Matt Welch bothered by a sore
shoulder, senior Ken Bowen is expected to make his first start of
the season. Welch practiced Thursday and both are expected to play.
</P>
<P>
   Nielsen becomes third tackle: Ryan Nielsen will be the third
defensive tackle in the rotation behind Ennis Davis and Aaron
Williams. Darren Collins could also play, but Hackett said he is
thinking about redshirting the JC transfer. Another possibility is
redshirt freshman Bobby DeMars.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
