<HEADLINE>
NHL 1998-1999: EASTERN CONFERENCE 
</HEADLINE>
 TAKES-BOS   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By KEVIN PAUL DUPONT AND NANCY L. MARRAPESE  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
 
ATLANTIC DIVISION 
 
NEW JERSEY DEVILS 
(FR)Coach: Robbie Ftorek 
(FR)Record: 48-23-11 (first) 
(FR)Key personnel changes: Acquired G Chris Terreri from Chicago
for a 1999 second- or third-round draft pick; acquired D Ken Sutton
from San Jose fort a 1999 fifth-round draft pick; lost C Doug
Gilmour, LW Steve Thomas, and D Doug Bodger as free agents; lost G
Mike Dunham in expansion draft. 
(FR)Outlook: Ftorek is behind the bench, replacing Jacques Lemaire.
Gone is veteran center Gilmour, who left for the Blackhawks in free
agency. The defensive system will remain in place, though Ftorek
has said he'll allow more offensive freedom. Could be a case of
taking the reins off the horse only to have him stay in the barn.
Martin Brodeur will always give them a chance. In this league, as
evidenced with Buffalo, a string goaltender is often enough. They
do, however, need to resolve their contract squabble with
defenseman Scott Niedermayer. 
 
 
 
NEW YORK ISLANDERS 
(FR)Coach: Mike Milbury 
(FR)Record: 30-41-11 (fourth) 
(FR)Key personnel changes: Signed G Marcel Cousineau, D Dean
Malkoc, D Barry Richter; lost D J.J. Daigneault and D Dennis Vaske
as free agents. 
(FR)Outlook: More turmoil on the island. There was an ownership
change, a lawsuit over whether the Nassau County Coliseum was safe
(a judge ruled it was), and more contract problems (an annual
occurrence it seems with Zigmund Palffy). Since the club has a
terrific coach in Milbury, a major trade with Toronto and Vancouver
(as rumored for the past two weeks) could be enough to shake the
Islanders out of their doldrums. 
 
 
 
NEW YORK RANGERS 
(FR)Coach: John Muckler 
(FR)Record: 25-39-18 (fifth) 
(FR)Key personnel changes: Acquired RW Mike Knuble from Detroit for
2000 third-round draft pick; signed LW Brent Fedyk, RW Scott
Fraser, RW John MacLean, D Zarley Zalapski, and G Kay Whitmore as
free agents; C Pat LaFontaine and D Bruce Driver retired. 
(FR)Outlook: When you have Wayne Gretzky and Mike Richter, it's
impossible to get too depressed. Niklas Sundstrom appears to be the
second line center, which is a good thing. Kevin Stevens has been
relegated to a checker by Muckler (still in the experimental
stages) and there's always Brian Leetch. With the new rules, the
Rangers should make a charge but may run out of gas by the end of
the season.  
 
 
 
PHILADELPHIA FLYERS 
(FR)Coach: Roger Neilson 
(FR)Record: 42-29-11 (second) 
(FR)Key personnel changes: Signed C Marc Bureau, G John
Vanbiesbrouck, and LW Valeri Zelepukin; lost G Sean Burke, D Paul
Coffey, and C Daniel Lacroix as free agents. 
(FR)Outlook: Is this the year? Some say it is, while others say it
will never be. The league and franchise have been waiting for Eric
Lindros to lead the Flyers to the promised land. He's armed with a
new contract, a burr in his saddle from comments made by general
manager Bob Clarke that Lindros needs to pick it up, and the best
roster in the East. Vanbiesbrouck could be the missing link. If
not, maybe goaltending wasn't the problem after all. 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
PITTSBURGH PENGUINS &QL; 
(FR)Coach: Kevin Constantine &QL; 
(FR)Record: 40-24-18 (first in Northeast) &QL; 
(FR)Key personnel changes: Acquired LW German Titov from Calgary;
acquired D Bobby Dollas from Edmonton; signed LW Todd Hlushko; lost
C Ron Francis, LW Joe Dziedzic, D Fredrik Olausson, C Ed Olczyk, G
Ken Wregget, and LW Alex Hicks as free agents. &QL; 
(FR)Outlook: This could be a very frustrating year for Jaromir
Jagr, who will have to perform without Mario Lemieux and Francis.
Truth is, the Penguins aren't a very good team. They've been hurt
badly by the ownership battle between Roger Marino and Howard
Baldwin. Could be a long season in the Steel City.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
NORTHEAST DIVISION &QL; 
 &QL; 
BOSTON BRUINS &QL; 
(FR)Coach: Pat Burns &QL; 
(FR)Record: 39-30-13 (second) &QL; 
(FR)Key personnel changes: Signed RW Peter Ferraro, C Chris Taylor,
and D Dennis Vaske as free agents; lost LW Mike Sullivan in
expansion draft. &QL; 
(FR)Outlook: The Bruins were a question mark at the start of last
season. This year, there are still a few puzzles on the horizon.
Byron Dafoe is a legitimate No. 1 goalie, Ray Bourque is still Ray
Bourque, but will the club be able to score consistently enough to
take it to the next level? Be assured Burns will get the most out
of his players. He'll either make or break Joe Thornton. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
BUFFALO SABRES &QL; 
(FR)Coach: Lindy Ruff &QL; 
(FR)Record: 36-29-17 (third) &QL; 
(FR)Key personnel changes: Signed LW Randy Cunneyworth, D James
Patrick, and G Dwayne Roloson; lost G Steve Shields as a free
agent; lost D Bob Boughner in expansion draft. &QL; 
(FR)Outlook: Dominik Hasek anchors a young team filled with players
whose names no one knows despite their slaying of Goliath
(Philadelphia) in the playoffs last year. When your leading scorer
has just 46 points ... well, you get the picture. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
MONTREAL CANADIENS &QL; 
(FR)Coach: Alain Vigneault &QL; 
(FR)Record: 37-32-13 (fourth) &QL; 
(FR)Key personnel changes: G Andy Moog retired; signed C Sergei
Zholtok; lost C Marc Bureau as a free agent. &QL; 
(FR)Outlook: Saku Koivu is signed (and therefore happy, we
presume), Vincent Damphousse has to have a better year than last
season. So where does that leave the Habs? It depends on
goaltending. The club has never really replaced Patrick Roy. In the
Eastern Conference, Montreal has enough to be competitive.  &QL; 
 &QL; 
OTTAWA SENATORS &QL; 
(FR)Coach: Jacques Martin &QL; 
(FR)Record: 34-33-15 (fifth) &QL; 
(FR)Key personnel changes: Signed RW Steve Leach and RW David
Oliver; lost LW Randy Cunneyworth, LW Denny Lambert, and RW Pat
Falloon as free agents. &QL; 
(FR)Outlook: A good coach and terrific young forwards but the
roster lacks depth. Once you get past oft-injured star Daniel
Alfredsson, Alexei Yashin, and Shawn McEachern, there isn't much
but scrappiness. That helps, but it's not enough. Is Damian Rhodes
that good? We'll see. This club, as it proved in the playoffs, has
the potential to make some noise.  &QL; 
 &QL; 
TORONTO MAPLE LEAFS &QL; 
(FR)Coach: Pat Quinn &QL; 
(FR)Record: 30-43-9 (sixth in Central) &QL; 
(FR)Key personnel changes: Signed G Curtis Joseph, LW Steve Thomas,
LW Scott Pearson, and LW Niklas Andersson; lost LW Wendel Clark as
a free agent; LW Nick Kypreos retired. &QL; 
(FR)Outlook: You have to love the decision to move the Maple Leafs
to the East. Well, OK, they were already in the East, but it was
good of the league to take them out of the Western Conference and
let them play where they belong. No-nonsense coach Quinn has
arrived, Joseph is in net, and the games between the Leafs and
Canadiens should be entertaining. Toronto is rebuilding but the
construction should be fun to watch.  &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
SOUTHEAST DIVISION &QL; 
 &QL; 
CAROLINA HURRICANES &QL; 
(FR)Coach: Paul Maurice &QL; 
(FR)Record: 33-41-8 (sixth in Northeast) &QL; 
(FR)Key personnel changes: Acquired D David Karpa and a 2000
fourth-round draft pick from Anaheim for D Kevin Haller and LW Stu
Grimson; signed C Ron Francis, G Arturs Irbe, and C Steve Martins;
lost LW Jeff Daniels as a free agent. &QL; 
(FR)Outlook: The return of Ron Francis to the franchise certainly
can't hurt. The 'Canes need Ray Sheppard to return to form. Keith
Primeau and Sami Kapanen are fine players but the fact is this is
only a so-so club.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
FLORIDA PANTHERS &QL; 
(FR)Coach: Terry Murray &QL; 
(FR)Record: 24-43-15 (sixth in Atlantic) &QL; 
(FR)Key personnel changes: Signed G Sean Burke; lost D Dallas
Eakins and G John Vanbiesbrouck as free agents. &QL; 
(FR)Outlook: The Panthers have a new building and new coach, but
will that be enough to inject life into a club that finished 12th
out of 13 teams in the conference last year? Will Kirk McLean, who
played for three teams last year, and Burke, who also played for
three teams, be enough to offset the loss of Vanbiesbrouck to the
Flyers? Look for a drought in southern Florida. &QL; 
 &UR; MORE &LR;  &QC;
