   TAKE-BOS  
 UNDATED: ... southern Florida.  (FR)Coach: Jacques Demers 
(FR)Record: 17-55-10 (seventh in Atlantic) 
(FR)Key personnel changes: Acquired G Mark Fitzpatrick and a 1999
fourth-round draft pick from Chicago for D Michal Sykora; acquired
C Craig Janney from Phoenix; acquired G Bill Ranford from
Washington; signed LW Wendel Clark and F Benoit Hogue; lost LW
Louie DeBrusk as a free agent. 
(FR)Outlook: The worst team in the league last year. They have
overhauled the roster, adding former Bruins Janney and Ranford and
veterans Clark and Hogue. Vincent Lecavalier, the first pick
overall, looks like a keeper and the feel good story of the year
could be John Cullen's comeback from cancer. The Lightning will be
better (they couldn't be worse), but not enough to contend. 
