<P>
   &UR; WASHINGTON (w) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; CLINTON-STRATEGY -- For years, Clinton has lived in a universe
of grand jury investigations, constant threats of additional
independent counsels and sniping from Capitol Hill. But this is
worse than anything else he has ever faced. By Brian McGrory. 1400
words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   COMA-CASE (Washington) _ Controversy still swirls around the
case of Hugh Finn, a coma patient state after being critically
injured in a car accident several years ago. His wife finally won
the right to have his feeding tube removed, but not before the
governor of Virginia and the courts weighed in. by Louse D. Palmer.
1500 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; COMMENTARY (k) &LR;
</P>
<P>
