   FLA-GOV-RACE (Miami) _ The Florida's governor's race: Buddy
MacKay, the Democratic lieutenant governor, is struggling to gain a
foothold against Jeb Bush, but the polls show a continuing double
digit lead for the Republican. By Mireya Navarro.
</P>
<P>
   WYO-GAY-BEATING (Laramie, Wyo.) _ A gay student at the
University of Wyoming was savagely beaten, burned and left to die
tied to a wooden fence outside Laramie, his head had been smashed
with a blunt object. Three University of Wyoming students were
arrested with more arrests expected. Police were investigating
whether the brutal beating was motivated by Shepard's sexual
orientation. By James Brooke.
