<HEADLINE>
MAN CHARGED WITH RAPE AFTER INCIDENT WITH 13-YEAR-OLD 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By RICHARD ESPINOZA and TONY RIZZO  
 c. 1998 Kansas City Star  
<TEXT>
<P>
   OLATHE, Kan. _ A Belton, Mo., man was charged Thursday with
having sexual contact with a 13-year-old Overland Park, Kan., girl
he allegedly met on the Internet.
</P>
<P>
   John Michael Wells, 29, was charged in Johnson County District
Court with one felony count of rape.
</P>
<P>
   District Judge Pro-tem Earle Jones followed the recommendations
of prosecutors and set a $50,000 bond. Wells posted the bond and
was released from the Johnson County Jail late Thursday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
   Under Kansas law, an adult who has sexual contact with a child
younger than 14 can be charged with rape even if there is no
allegation that force was used.
</P>
<P>
   Wells and the girl began communicating with each other in an
Internet chat room and agreed to meet this week in Johnson County,
Overland Park police said.
</P>
<P>
   Wells allegedly drove to Overland Park on Tuesday afternoon and
picked the girl up after class at a Blue Valley School District
middle school. He is accused of having sexual contact with her in a
grocery store parking lot. He dropped her off near her home.
</P>
<P>
   Police said the girl told friends and the friends reported it to
a school resource officer. Police learned that Wells and the girl
were supposed to meet again Wednesday, they said.
</P>
<P>
   Officers arrested Wells about 4:15 p.m. Wednesday while he was
driving, allegedly looking for the girl for their meeting.
</P>
<P>
   Authorities said that Wells had no criminal record. He faces a
sentence of about 16 years in prison if convicted.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
