   &UR; THE CLINTON IMPEACHMENT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-IMPEACH (Washington) -- One day after an historic vote
to launch an impeachment inquiry of President Clinton, an internal
Republican debate begins over how to proceed, with some GOP members
suggesting that the hearings will focus mostly on whether Clinton
was engaged in a coverup of his relationship with Monica S.
Lewinsky. By Michael Kranish. 1300 words. (w coding)
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-SOUTH (Washington) -- One is a black Democrat
representing a majority-white district in Georgia, the other a
white Democrat from a South Carolina district that is more than 30
percent black. Both are moderates facing tough reelection battles.
Any impeachment vote can impact important constituencies. By Ann
Scales 1000 words. (w and a)
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-APATHY (Los Angeles) _ Both dull and infuriating, the
Clinton impeachment story gets easier and easier not to pay
attention to, even for those who feel guilty about tuning out
history. 1300 words. By Lynda Gorov. (a)
</P>
