<P>
   CLINTON-CAMPAIGN (Washington) _ President Clinton is sitting out
much of the most important election of his life, largely foregoing
the barnstorming that presidents usually undertake in midterm
elections. With the threat of impeachment hanging over his head, he
plans stops in only seven or eight states in this campaign. By
STEWART M. POWELL. (Already filed.)
</P>
