   NATIONAL (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   INDIAN-GAMING (Temecula, Calif.) _ It's expected to be the most
expensive ballot proposition in California history. At stake is the
future of Indian casino gaming, which operates illegally in a state
where Las Vegas has traditionally drawn 35 percent of its business.
Nevada gaming interests will spend millions to try to defeat the
proposition, but ironically, the once impoverished Indian tribes
will probably spend the most to defend it. By KIM COBB. (Already
filed.)
</P>
<P>
   FERAL-CATS (College Station, Texas) _ By day, the sprawling
Texas A&AMP;M University campus almost buzzes with chaos and excitement
as more than 43,000 Aggies fly to classes and meetings, pursuing
their dream of higher education. But when darkness falls and the
students retreat, the cats appear. From basement, window sill and
drain pipe, they come. Three hundred of them, by the best estimate.
By ALLAN TURNER. (Already filed.)
</P>
