<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LADN-SPORTS-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following sports
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Oct. 10 and thereafter. For questions about stories, resends or
inquiries, call Joe Jares at (818) 713-3602. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
FBC-UCLA (Tucson, Ariz.) _ Advance to the UCLA at Arizona game.
Call it trouble in Tucson. The Bruins haven't beaten the Wildcats
there since 1988. &QL; 
By Jon Wilner. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
HKN-KINGS (Edmonton) _ Profile of the Los Angeles Kings, who begin
their season Saturday night against the Edmonton Oilers.
</P>
<P>
   By Roger Phillips/Long Beach Press-Telegram. (Will move on the
``s'' sports file.) &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
FBC-USC (Los Angeles) _ Advance to the USC-California game at the
Coliseum.
</P>
<P>
   By Scott Wolf. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
FBC-MODESTI-COLUMN (Tucson, Ariz.) _ On UCLA having to face Arizona
hysteria on Saturday. The Wildcats have their first sellout in two
years, and there isn't a rental car or hotel room to be found in
Tucson. &QL; 
By Kevin Modesti. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
FBC-CSUN (Los Angeles) _ Advance to the Cal State
Northridge-Montana game, at Northridge's field. &QL; 
By Brian Dohn. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
SOC-GALAXY (Pasadena, Calif.) _ Advance to Saturday's first game of
the Western Conference finals vs. Chicago, in the Rose Bowl. &QL; 
By Scott French/Long Beach Press-Telegram. (Will move on the ``s''
sports file.)
</P>
