<SLUG> BC-NASATECH-CHART-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NASATECH-CHART 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  By LAURA GOLDBERG 
c.1998 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NASA technology that could be adapted for commercial use will be
on display during Johnson Space Center's Inspection98. Here are a
few examples:
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
Cable scanner: checks cable continuity without disconnecting the
cable. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; Space mission use: provides a nonintrusive system for testing
cable in Space Shuttle.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; Commercial use: could be used in automotive, cable TV and
computer network industries. System is accurate, low cost and
portable.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Oxygen prebreathe for extravehicular activities: Astronauts
breathe oxygen before activities outside of spacecraft to help
prevent decompression sickness, or the bends. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; Space mission use: procedure developed reduces amount of time
need to get ready for an extravehicular activity.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; Commercial use: could be used by commercial deep-sea divers
and some aspects by recreational scuba divers.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Station orbiter multibody berthing analysis tool: uses advanced
computational algorithms to solve spacecraft dynamics &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Space mission use: applied to various mission simulations
including Space Station, Space Shuttle and docking/berthing
operations.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; Commercial use: can be applied to image reconstruction and
digital signal processing. Could be used in designing medicines,
where drug molecules interact with disease molecules.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Imaging technologies for spaceflight operations: image analysis
software that analyzes motion &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Space mission use: measures motions of space vehicle structures
using video imagery.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; Commercial use: wide-range of applications including for
automotive, transportation and manufacturing industries.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Intelligent fault diagnosis technology: draws conclusions based
on information it receives such as sensor data, observations and
environmental conditions &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Space mission use: diagnosing problems of spacecraft.
</P>
<P>
   Commercial use: software has a generic design that be adapted
for other uses including automotive and medical diagnosis; and
chemical process and power plant monitoring. &QL; 
 &QL; 
XXXXEND OF STORY &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
