   (NYT11) CAPE KENNEDY SPACE CENTER, Fla. -- Oct. 09, 1998 --
SCI-SHUTTLE-GLENN, 10-09 -- John Glenn and the crew of Space
Shuttle Mission STS-95, scheduled to launch on Oct. 29th, do a
dress rehearsal walk out to the Shuttle for a count down test
Friday. Curt Brown, at right front with mustache is the mission's
commander. (Keith Meyers/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT10) WASHINGTON -- 0ct. 09, 1998 -- CONGRESS-HEALTH, 10-09 --
House and Senate Democrats join President Clinton at the White
House after Republicans defeated an effort to get a ``Patients Bill
of Rights'' enacted. They are, from left, Sen. Ted Kennedy, Rep.
David Obey, Rep. David Bonior, Sens. Barbara Mikulski and Tom
Daschle, Clinton, Reps. Charles Rangel, Steny Hoyer, Nita Lowey,
Richard Gephardt and Robert Menendez. (Stephen Crowley/New York
Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT9) NEW YORK -- 0ct. 09, 1998 -- ADV. FOR SUN., OCT. 11 --
NY-DERMATOLOGIST, 10-09 -- Dr. Pat Wexler has earned a reputation
for being a skin genie as well as a comfy, if sometimes stern,
Jewish mother. Dr. Wexler began her career as an internist,
specializing in infectious diseases. But after deciding that it was
too emotionally wearing to treat seriously ill patients, she went
back for a residency in dermatology. (Chester Higgins Jr./New York
Times Photo) *LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT8) FALL RIVER, Mass. -- 0ct. 09, 1998 -- ADV. FOR SUN., OCT.
11 -- MUTFUND-WINNERS-2, 10-09 -- Irving Levine, manager of the
$87.5 million Copley fund, in front of the original Berkshire
Hathaway building which was once a mill. Levine's fund has about 55
percent of its portfolio in a mix of telephone, gas and electric
companies, which pay the high dividends many investors seek in
uncertain times. (Kirsten Elstner/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
