<P>
   (NYT5) ANAHEIM, Calif. -- 0ct. 09, 1998 -- ADV. FOR SUN., OCT.11
- - BIZ-PROFILE, 10-09 -- Peter de Jager, a former programmer from
the Toronto area, is widely regarded as having been pivotal in
giving the warning to the computer world about the Y2K probplem.
Since writing an essay five years ago titled ``Doomsday 2000'' for
Computerworld, a trade magazine, de Jager has become something of a
folk hero in his crusade to publicize the problem. (Marissa
Roth/New York Times Photo)
