executive of Mattel, has tried to change its corporate culture into
one more appropriate for a toy maker. Managers, for example, might
perform skits to communicate with employees, while Ms. Barad
incorporates the use of these life-size Ken and Barbie dolls.
(Monica Almeida/New York Times Photo)
