</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Maryland heads up against Clemson over weekend
 &HT;    By Wendy Parker
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _
</P>
<P>
   MARYLAND VS. CLEMSON
</P>
<P>
   When, where: Today, noon, Memorial Stadium, Clemson, S.C.
</P>
<P>
   Series: Clemson leads 24-20-2.
</P>
<P>
   Records: Maryland 2-3, 0-2 ACC; Clemson 1-4, 0-3 ACC.
</P>
<P>
   Game notes: The Tigers, who celebrate homecoming, have won nine
of the last 10 meetings in the series, while Maryland last won in
Death Valley in 1985. . . . Both seek their first conference wins.
. . . Clemson has lost just two homecoming games in the last 27
years. . . . Clemson's Antwan Edwards is fifth in the nation in
kickoff returns, averaging 37 yards per attempt. . . . All of
Maryland's losses have been to Top 20 teams: Florida State,
Virginia and West Virginia.
</P>
<P>
   PITTSBURGH VS. NORTH CAROLINA
</P>
<P>
   When, where: Today, 1:30 p.m., Kenan Stadium, Chapel Hill, N.C.
</P>
<P>
   Series: Tied 2-2.
</P>
<P>
   Records: Pittsburgh 2-2; North Carolina 1-3.
</P>
<P>
   Game notes: The Tar Heels, who finally won a game last week
against Clemson, play their last non-conference game. . . .
Although sixth in the ACC in total offense, freshman QB Ron Curry
was replaced last week by ailing senior Oscar Davenport, who guided
UNC's comeback victory. . . . Once the pride of its defense, the
Tar Heel secondary currently ranks last against the pass in the
ACC, giving up an average of 144 yards per game, and has just two
interceptions. . . . UNC's chief offensive problem is rushing,
which is dead last in the ACC at 94.5 yards.
</P>
<P>
   FLORIDA STATE VS. MIAMI
</P>
<P>
   When, where: Today, 3:30 p.m., Orange Bowl, Miami
</P>
<P>
   Series: Miami leads 23-18.
</P>
<P>
   Records: Florida State 4-1; Miami 3-1.
</P>
<P>
   Game notes: The Seminoles have won their last four, while Miami
is coming off an unexpected off-week following the postponement of
a scheduled home game with UCLA due to Hurricane Georges. . . .
Last year in Tallahassee, FSU romped to a 47-0 win, its third
straight over the Hurricanes. The Seminoles have won those games by
an average of 29.7 points. . . . FSU committed nine turnovers in
its first two games but has turned the ball over just twice in its
last three outings. . . . The Seminoles were limited to just one
touchdown and five field goals in a 24-10 win at Maryland last
week.
</P>
<P>
   DUKE VS. WAKE FOREST
</P>
<P>
   When, where: Today, 6:30 p.m., Groves Stadium, Winston-Salem,
N.C.
</P>
<P>
   Series: Duke leads 51-25-2.
</P>
<P>
   Records: Duke 2-3, 0-3 ACC; Wake Forest 2-2, 1-0 ACC.
</P>
<P>
   Game notes: The Deacons are coming off a loss last week to
Division I-AA Appalachian State, while the Blue Devils absorbed a
record 21st consecutive ACC loss at Georgia Tech. . . . Wake has
beaten Duke each of the last two years. . . . Wake's passing
offense ranks (236 yards a game) only behind that of N.C. State and
Florida State in the ACC, but the Deacons are last in third down
conversions, making just 24 of 63 opportunities.
</P>
