 &HT;    Mississippi State meets Auburn on Saturday
 &HT;    By Leo Willingham
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _
</P>
<P>
   MISSISSIPPI STATE VS. AUBURN
</P>
<P>
   When, where: Today, 12:30 p.m., Scott Field, Starkville, Miss.
</P>
<P>
   Series: Auburn leads 50-19-2.
</P>
<P>
   Records: Mississippi State 3-1, 2-0 SEC West; Auburn 1-3, 1-2
SEC West.
</P>
<P>
   Game notes: Injured players Barrin Simpson and Kendall Roberson
and suspended backup quarterback Rob Morgan are expected to return
for Mississippi State after an open date last weekend. . . . Auburn
ranks 11th in the conference in total offense while Mississippi
State is second in the SEC and sixth in the nation in passing
defense.
</P>
<P>
   VANDERBILT VS. WESTERN MICHIGAN
</P>
<P>
   When, where: Today, 2 p.m., Vanderbilt Stadium, Nashville.
</P>
<P>
   Series: First meeting.
</P>
<P>
   Records: Vanderbilt 0-4, Western Michigan 2-3.
</P>
<P>
   Game notes: Vanderbilt had won five straight non-conference
games before last week's 19-16 loss at TCU. . . . Vanderbilt has a
6-0 record against teams in the current Mid-American Conference. .
. . Western Michigan coach Gary Darnell served as defensive
coordinator at Florida in 1988-89 and was the interim head coach
during the last seven games of the 1989 season.
</P>
<P>
   ALABAMA VS. MISSISSIPPI
</P>
<P>
   When, where: Today, 3 p.m., Bryant-Denny Stadium, Tuscaloosa,
Ala.
</P>
<P>
   Series: Alabama leads 36-7-2.
</P>
<P>
   Records: Alabama 2-2, 1-2 SEC West; Mississippi 4-1, 2-1 SEC
West.
</P>
<P>
   Game notes: Alabama has won seven straight and 12 of the last 14
games in the series, including a 29-20 victory at Mississippi last
season. . . . The Rebels are off to their best start since 1991. .
. . Mississippi has scored at least 30 points in its four victories
while Alabama, which scored 70 points in its two wins, has only 16
in its last two losses.
</P>
<P>
   MEMPHIS VS. ARKANSAS
</P>
<P>
   When, where: Today, 3:30 p.m., Liberty Bowl Memorial Stadium,
Memphis.
</P>
<P>
   Series: Memphis leads 3-1.
</P>
<P>
   Records: Memphis 0-4; Arkansas 4-0.
</P>
<P>
   Game notes: This is the last non-conference game for Arkansas
before ending the season with six straight SEC games, including
four on the road. . . . Woodstock's Neil Suber is the leading
passer for Memphis, which is coached by former Georgia Tech and
Alabama assistant Rip Scherer.
</P>
<P>
   KENTUCKY VS. SOUTH CAROLINA
</P>
<P>
   When, where: Today, 7 p.m., Commonwealth Stadium, Lexington, Ky.
</P>
<P>
   Series: Tied 4-4-1.
</P>
<P>
   Records: Kentucky 3-2, 0-2 SEC East; South Carolina 1-4, 0-3 SEC
East.
</P>
<P>
   Game notes: Kentucky has lost its last two games while South
Carolina has dropped four straight since winning the season opener.
The Gamecocks have not lost five straight since 1992. . . .
Kentucky's Tim Couch has passed for 2,076 yards and 19 touchdowns,
but the Wildcats hope to exploit South Carolina's run defense which
ranks 11th in the SEC allowing 193 yards per game.
</P>
<P>
   FLORIDA VS. LSU
</P>
<P>
   When, where: Today, 7 p.m., Florida Field, Gainesville.
</P>
<P>
   Series: Florida leads 22-19-3.
</P>
<P>
   Records: Florida 4-1, 2-1 SEC East; LSU 3-1, 1-1 SEC West.
</P>
<P>
   Game notes: Both teams were preseason favorites to win their
respective division titles and meet for the SEC championship. After
early conference losses, both teams need a victory to remain in the
race for the title. . . . The quarterback shuffle has ended at
Florida with Jesse Palmer earning the starting nod. . . . Florida
leads the SEC and ranks third nationally in rushing defense (71
yards per game) while LSU's strength is its running attack, which
ranks second in the SEC.
</P>
